783
01:17:02,827 --> 01:17:06,548
Their leader Dr. Heinrich Dwyer
became convinced

784
01:17:06,705 --> 01:17:09,208
that Evey could reincarnate their idol.

785
01:17:09,834 --> 01:17:12,212
On June 6th, 1954,

786
01:17:12,545 --> 01:17:15,515
Dr. Dwyer claimed that
Evey had received a message that

787
01:17:15,589 --> 01:17:18,559
the Lilitu should lock themselves
inside this building.

788
01:17:19,260 --> 01:17:23,766
A massive fire destroyed the building
that night, killing everyone inside.

789
01:17:25,224 --> 01:17:26,225
Sir.

790
01:17:28,060 --> 01:17:29,061
Sir.

791
01:17:31,564 --> 01:17:33,532
Everyone including Evey Dwyer,

792
01:17:34,525 --> 01:17:37,404
who was born with a birthmark, a sigil.

793
01:17:39,280 --> 01:17:41,908
Evey Dwyer for some reason is

794
01:17:42,032 --> 01:17:44,251
a force that possesses Jane Harper.

795
01:17:44,368 --> 01:17:45,415
Oh, my God.

796
01:17:46,954 --> 01:17:49,582
Evey's gonna do to us
what she did to the Lilitu.

797
01:17:51,542 --> 01:17:53,761
- She's a...
- A demonic spirit?

798
01:17:55,045 --> 01:17:57,594
Evil begetting evil for the sake of evil

799
01:17:57,715 --> 01:18:00,093
until the end of all times?

800
01:18:00,593 --> 01:18:03,312
Maybe even old Beelzebub himself.

801
01:18:04,930 --> 01:18:06,932
Do any of these seriously work for you?

802
01:18:07,057 --> 01:18:09,435
- They all work.
- Or...

803
01:18:10,102 --> 01:18:11,194
Or what?

804
01:18:11,270 --> 01:18:13,272
The rational explanation.

805
01:18:13,898 --> 01:18:16,071
That Jane somehow
found out about this cult.

806
01:18:16,192 --> 01:18:17,284
When she was four?

807
01:18:17,443 --> 01:18:20,283
She heard it at the breakfast table,
her parents read it in a newspaper.

808
01:18:20,362 --> 01:18:22,114
You make anything fit into your hypothesis.

809
01:18:22,281 --> 01:18:24,875
This only strengthens
my hypothesis actually, Harry.

810
01:18:25,451 --> 01:18:28,204
When we ask Jane to go deep
she plucked the name

811
01:18:28,287 --> 01:18:30,790
Evey Dwyer out of the deepest
recesses of her mind.

812
01:18:31,457 --> 01:18:34,586
That is what she is manifesting,
that is what you call her "possession!"

813
01:18:34,710 --> 01:18:38,806
God, you're the one who's possessed,
Coupland, by your own bullshit!

814
01:18:42,635 --> 01:18:44,228
Who is Evey Dwyer?

815
01:18:46,138 --> 01:18:48,391
You know about her, don't you?

816
01:18:49,558 --> 01:18:52,812
You found out about her
or somebody told you about her.

817
01:18:52,978 --> 01:18:55,857
But you knew about her before I found you.

818
01:18:57,650 --> 01:18:58,993
Answer me!

819
01:18:59,735 --> 01:19:00,987
Hey, hey, hey!

820
01:19:01,070 --> 01:19:02,162
Speak, damn you!

821
01:19:05,532 --> 01:19:06,875
Brian!

822
01:19:08,869 --> 01:19:10,462
Don't you touch her again.

823
01:19:10,579 --> 01:19:12,081
But you will, won't you?

824
01:19:13,332 --> 01:19:15,505
Maybe you can screw the truth out of her.

825
01:19:18,587 --> 01:19:22,182
Krissi, Harry, stay or leave, your choice.

826
01:19:22,299 --> 01:19:25,519
You, cameraman or Lancelot,

827
01:19:25,636 --> 01:19:27,559
or whoever the hell you think you are,

828
01:19:27,680 --> 01:19:29,682
I want you and your gear gone tonight.

829
01:19:31,016 --> 01:19:34,316
The footage handed over. Every frame.

830
01:20:06,176 --> 01:20:07,348
What are we gonna do?

831
01:20:08,053 --> 01:20:10,806
I'm leaving. I'm taking Jane with me.

832
01:20:11,473 --> 01:20:14,647
- He'll never let you.
- And even if he did, what then?

833
01:20:15,144 --> 01:20:17,192
Find her help, professional help.

834
01:20:17,271 --> 01:20:20,195
What kind of help? An exorcist?

835
01:20:20,357 --> 01:20:23,486
She's not staying here, not with him.

836
01:20:24,403 --> 01:20:27,907
I need your help, I need your car for starters.

837
01:20:29,908 --> 01:20:34,084
Do you seriously believe that
Joseph still knows what he's doing?

838
01:20:40,836 --> 01:20:42,554
It won't make a bit of difference.

839
01:21:13,786 --> 01:21:18,257
<i>- Get it out! Get it out!
- David!</i>

840
01:22:01,834 --> 01:22:03,461
<i>Leave me alone!</i>

841
01:22:04,920 --> 01:22:07,014
<i>Tell him to leave me alone, Daddy!</i>

842
01:22:08,424 --> 01:22:12,679
<i>I'm trying to find him, Daddy.
I can't find him.</i>

843
01:22:14,638 --> 01:22:16,686
<i>I don't want to do this anymore, Daddy.</i>

844
01:22:27,025 --> 01:22:28,618
<i>I'm sorry, David.</i>

845
01:22:32,656 --> 01:22:34,533
<i>I'm trying to help you.</i>

846
01:23:06,315 --> 01:23:08,317
If only I had more time with him.

847
01:23:09,735 --> 01:23:11,203
If only she...

848
01:23:11,320 --> 01:23:13,914
- David Q. was your son.
- You deceived me!

849
01:23:14,031 --> 01:23:17,706
No, Jane, try and understand.

850
01:23:19,661 --> 01:23:21,663
I've dedicated my entire life to this.

851
01:23:21,747 --> 01:23:24,045
I'm absolutely certain that I am correct.

852
01:23:25,667 --> 01:23:30,173
I can cure you. Please, I'm begging you.

853
01:23:32,716 --> 01:23:34,184
Believe in me.

854
01:23:39,932 --> 01:23:41,775
We believed in you, Joseph.

855
01:23:42,601 --> 01:23:44,069
You bastard!

856
01:23:44,144 --> 01:23:46,112
- You lied to us.
- You used me!

857
01:23:46,230 --> 01:23:48,071
- I gave you everything!
- Don't you touch her!

858
01:23:48,398 --> 01:23:51,868
Harry, stop! Harry, Harry, Harry, stop it!

859
01:23:54,279 --> 01:23:55,531
- Harry!
- What the fuck?

860
01:24:10,629 --> 01:24:12,097
Jesus!

861
01:24:12,548 --> 01:24:13,970
- Get out of here!
- Krissi, wait!

862
01:24:19,805 --> 01:24:20,977
Krissi!

863
01:24:22,307 --> 01:24:23,399
Harry!

864
01:24:29,106 --> 01:24:30,107
Krissi!

865
01:24:31,233 --> 01:24:34,112
Krissi! Krissi!

866
01:24:34,820 --> 01:24:36,948
Krissi, open up! Krissi!

867
01:24:37,781 --> 01:24:39,909
Krissi, hold on, I'm coming!

868
01:24:40,993 --> 01:24:43,416
- Krissi!
- Krissi!

869
01:24:45,664 --> 01:24:46,756
Krissi!

870
01:24:48,417 --> 01:24:49,634
It's got me!

871
01:24:52,504 --> 01:24:54,506
No, no, no!

872
01:25:11,690 --> 01:25:12,862
Krissi...

873
01:25:38,216 --> 01:25:39,342
Jane?

874
01:25:40,302 --> 01:25:41,554
Jane?

875
01:25:46,892 --> 01:25:48,894
She was the only survivor.

876
01:25:50,979 --> 01:25:52,572
They must have
kept it out of the newspapers

877
01:25:52,689 --> 01:25:55,067
so she'd have a chance at a normal life.

878
01:25:57,194 --> 01:26:00,915
They changed her name.
A family took her in.

879
01:26:02,407 --> 01:26:06,082
But the past became
a bad dream that lived in Evey like a virus.

880
01:26:07,412 --> 01:26:11,713
It drove her mad, she forgot everything.

881
01:26:25,097 --> 01:26:26,724
You're Evey Dwyer.

882
01:26:27,933 --> 01:26:30,106
No wonder it's never leaving me.

883
01:26:31,603 --> 01:26:34,231
The truth was always
there right in front of me.

884
01:26:35,440 --> 01:26:36,942
I was born this way.

885
01:26:39,528 --> 01:26:40,620
And that's how I'll die.

886
01:26:40,862 --> 01:26:43,285
No, don't do that, don't...

887
01:26:43,949 --> 01:26:46,873
All my life I felt
there's something burning inside of me.

888
01:26:46,952 --> 01:26:48,750
Just let me help you.

889
01:26:48,870 --> 01:26:51,373
I don't deserve to live.
I killed all those people.

890
01:26:51,456 --> 01:26:53,458
Come with me. I can help you.

891
01:26:53,625 --> 01:26:55,969
I can't be saved!

892
01:27:04,803 --> 01:27:06,555
Jane, Jane!

893
01:27:07,222 --> 01:27:08,599
I'm not Jane!

894
01:27:19,818 --> 01:27:21,070
You okay?

895
01:27:23,321 --> 01:27:24,698
Is she out?

896
01:27:25,657 --> 01:27:27,000
I think so.

897
01:27:45,051 --> 01:27:49,522
The patient we knew as Jane Harper
was born Evey Dwyer.

898
01:27:50,223 --> 01:27:53,227
As a child
she was indoctrinated into an occult group

899
01:27:53,518 --> 01:27:57,022
and made to believe
she could reincarnate their idol.

900
01:27:57,773 --> 01:28:02,529
The damage that wrought on her mind
was severe.

901
01:28:02,694 --> 01:28:05,538
The patient has expressed
on numerous occasions

902
01:28:05,697 --> 01:28:08,371
a suicidal ideation, a death wish.

903
01:28:08,450 --> 01:28:09,747
Joseph, you're gonna kill her!

904
01:28:09,868 --> 01:28:14,374
Yes. But I'm going to bring her back.

905
01:28:15,123 --> 01:28:18,548
Ten cc's of adrenaline injected
directly into the heart should do the trick.

906
01:28:18,710 --> 01:28:20,257
You're not gonna get away with this.

907
01:28:20,378 --> 01:28:23,723
Of course I'm not gonna get away with it!
Are you insane?

908
01:28:24,216 --> 01:28:26,218
There are two dead people in this house.

909
01:28:26,301 --> 01:28:28,554
- Untie, just untie...
- Quiet!

910
01:28:29,679 --> 01:28:31,522
You have a part to play in this.

911
01:28:32,265 --> 01:28:35,269
You are the reason
she's going to want to come back.

912
01:28:37,395 --> 01:28:39,523
- Jane, dear.
- Jane?

913
01:28:40,440 --> 01:28:42,989
- Can you hear me?
- Jane!

914
01:28:43,318 --> 01:28:45,070
Can you hear my voice?

915
01:28:45,654 --> 01:28:49,409
- Joseph...
- Yes, dear, it's me.

916
01:28:50,033 --> 01:28:53,037
I want you to release Evey one last time.

917
01:28:53,578 --> 01:28:55,455
- Joseph, leave her alone!
- Be quiet!

918
01:28:55,997 --> 01:28:58,546
I will take photograms
of your bio-electric activity

919
01:28:58,667 --> 01:29:00,761
<i>as</i> Evey leaves your body forever.

920
01:29:00,836 --> 01:29:04,591
We will have scientific evidence.
It'll all be documented on film.

921
01:29:05,173 --> 01:29:06,174
Jane!

922
01:29:09,427 --> 01:29:12,351
All right, here we go.

923
01:29:12,472 --> 01:29:13,473
Jane!

924
01:29:14,307 --> 01:29:16,526
Joseph, don't you dare.

925
01:29:16,810 --> 01:29:21,031
Joseph! Joseph! Joseph!

926
01:29:22,440 --> 01:29:24,943
Jane! Joseph!

927
01:29:29,656 --> 01:29:30,657
Jane.

928
01:29:32,534 --> 01:29:35,458
Just give her the shot, Joseph! Get up!

929
01:29:39,624 --> 01:29:41,626
Joseph, give her the adrenaline!

930
01:29:41,751 --> 01:29:44,129
Aren't you just a little bit curious?

931
01:29:46,047 --> 01:29:48,141
Please just give her the adrenaline now.

932
01:29:49,384 --> 01:29:52,558
- Joseph, do it!
- Not until Evey arrives.

933
01:30:37,098 --> 01:30:39,601
Jane? Jane, just... What?

934
01:31:02,207 --> 01:31:04,050
Jesus, Jane, come on!

935
01:31:09,589 --> 01:31:10,841
Jane, Jane.

936
01:31:11,424 --> 01:31:14,018
Jane, look at me. It's me.

937
01:31:33,571 --> 01:31:35,790
- Jane.
- I'm sorry.

938
01:31:48,169 --> 01:31:50,263
Jane. Jane.

939
01:31:51,339 --> 01:31:52,682
Jane, open the door.

940
01:31:54,134 --> 01:31:55,135
Jane...

941
01:31:55,385 --> 01:31:56,386
Jane!

942
01:31:58,304 --> 01:32:00,022
Jane, open the door!

943
01:32:13,194 --> 01:32:14,195
Jane!

944
01:32:15,113 --> 01:32:17,115
Open the door, Jane!

945
01:32:17,407 --> 01:32:19,205
Jane, please don't!

946
01:32:19,909 --> 01:32:21,877
Jane, talk to me!

947
01:32:30,670 --> 01:32:32,672
Jane! Jane!

948
01:32:48,396 --> 01:32:50,148
<i>There was a fire.</i>

949
01:32:53,318 --> 01:32:54,911
How did they die, Brian?

950
01:32:57,155 --> 01:32:58,657
It's in here.

951
01:33:02,535 --> 01:33:04,162
In here.

952
01:33:05,747 --> 01:33:08,216
- It's in here.
- It's not in there.

953
01:33:08,833 --> 01:33:10,506
All the film's destroyed.

954
01:33:16,007 --> 01:33:18,305
You killed them, didn't you?

955
01:33:24,474 --> 01:33:27,273
Tell us what really happened.

956
01:33:39,155 --> 01:33:40,202
What is that?

